👉  ARRAYS IN JAVA

👉  Definition

An array is a collection of similar types of data stored in contiguous memory locations.
All elements in an array must be of the same data type.
Arrays are used to store multiple values using a single variable name.

````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````
👉 Need of Array

If we want to store marks of 5 students, instead of creating 5 different variables like:

int m1 = 85;
int m2 = 90;
int m3 = 78;
int m4 = 88;
int m5 = 92;

We can use an array to store all marks together.

````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````
👉 Declaration and Creation of Array

Syntax:

datatype[] arrayName = new datatype[size];
OR
datatype arrayName[] = new datatype[size];

Example: int[] marks = new int[5];

Here,
int → data type
marks → array name
5 → size of array

````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````
👉 Indexing in Array

• Array index starts from 0.
• Last index = size − 1.

For an array of size 5:

Index: 0 1 2 3 4

````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````
👉 Assigning Values to Array

marks[0] = 85;
marks[1] = 90;
marks[2] = 78;
marks[3] = 88;
marks[4] = 92;

````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````
👉 Accessing / Printing Array Elements

Using for loop:

for(int i = 0; i < 5; i++){
    System.out.println(marks[i]);
}

````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````
👉 Direct Initialization of Array

We can also initialize array at the time of declaration:
int[] marks = {85, 90, 78, 88, 92};

````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````
👉 Length of Array

The length of an array can be found using:

arrayName.length

Example:

public class Arrays{
    public static void main(String[] args){
        int marks []={34,45,56,67,89};
        System.out.println(marks.length);
    }
}

OUTPUT : 5

````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````
👉 Important Points

1.    Arrays store homogeneous (same type) data.
2.    Array size must be specified at the time of creation.
3.    Memory is allocated in contiguous locations.
4.    Index always starts from 0.
5.    Once created, array size cannot be changed.

